review_blob: Amber-orange in colour, pours with a foamy  head. Nice earthy, fruity aroma.  Very easy drinking ale, nice balance between slight fruity taste and mildly bitter finish.
Hazy orange in colour, pours with a medium head.  Starts very sweet but finishes smooth and dry.  Nice raspberry flavor with oaky undertones.  One of the nicest raspberry beers I have had.
Brown in colour, pours with a stiff foamy head.  Fruity aroma with a hint of wood and roasted malt.  Moderately sweet in taste with a bitter finish.  Roasted malt and smokey flavors are present.
Golden yellow in colour, pours with a foamy long-lasting head.  Fruity aroma with a smooth, sweet taste.
Golden yellow in colour, slight citrus taste with a clean finish.  A nice summer beer.
Pale yellow in colour, skunky slightly citrus aroma.  Flat, pale and weak, nothing special in this beer.
Almost black in colour with a slight reddish tone.  Fruity aroma, hint of raisins and chocolate.  Very sweet in taste with a bit too much carbonation.  The Jolt cola of the stout world...
Orange-yellow in colour, kind of hazy.  Subtle apricot flavour matches nicely with the clean wheat beer taste.  Not too fruity, very refreshing drink.
Pitch black in colour, rich and velvety in taste.  Slightly bitter chocolate flavour.  One of the best beers I have had.
One of my favourite beers.  Deep black in colour, rich and velvety on the tongue.  Smoky, slightly bitter taste, smooth finish.
Amber in colour, subtle fruity aroma with a  hint of skunkiness.  Mild fruity taste, sweet finish.  Not as good as Mort Subite gueuze which I also tried.
Slight orange colour, sweet fruity flavour.  Better than the St Louis gueuze I also tried.
Pale yellow colour, slight ginger aroma and taste.  Very little head with moderate carbonation, sweet and light.
